        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 12 at 12:19AM CDT by NWS Austin/San Antonio TX</headline>
        <description>At 1219 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Cliff to Leon Valley. These storms were
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Antonio, San Antonio Int Airport, Leon Valley, Helotes, Shavano
Park, Hollywood Park, Cross Mountain, Lackland AFB, Cliff, Leon
Springs, The Dominion, Government Canyon State Natural Area, Rio
Medina, Sea World, Castle Hills, Balcones Heights, Hill Country
Village, Grey Forest, San Geronimo, and Fiesta Texas.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with these storms.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
